          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is a compendium of cure-amulets meant to be carried about or worn as protective charms. Contains diagrams (yantras) of cosmologies, the human body, deities, and animals along with various mantras to be recited during the performance of healing rites and to ward of danger. Such diagrammatic manuscripts are found throughout South Asia on palm leaves or sheets of copper.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="sin" otherLangs="tam mal">In Sinhalese, Jaffna Tamil, and Malayalam</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Sinhalese protective charm yantras</title>
            </msItem>
          </msContents>
